1
00:00:00,000 --> 00:00:07,760
All characters and events in this series are fictional
and created solely for entertainment purposes.
Viewer discretion is advised.

2
00:01:41,200 --> 00:01:42,920
I have something to confess to you, Sun.

3
00:01:42,920 --> 00:01:46,440
P'Flint… are you about to say that the person you met...

4
00:01:46,440 --> 00:01:47,759
was P’Jan?

5
00:01:47,759 --> 00:01:48,840
I’m sorry…

6
00:01:49,840 --> 00:01:51,680
I’m sorry for misunderstanding you all this time.

7
00:01:53,320 --> 00:01:56,920
Hello, Khun Rafah. You have a package delivered.

8
00:01:58,120 --> 00:02:02,640
It looks like the person who took those photos is
someone very close to Khun Rafah and Sun.

9
00:02:02,640 --> 00:02:04,320
P’Sun, would you like to go rest for a bit?

10
00:02:04,320 --> 00:02:06,560
Since my condo is close to yours anyway.

11
00:02:07,840 --> 00:02:10,600
How did you know where my condo is?

12
00:02:11,880 --> 00:02:14,040
JanJao, open the door right now!

13
00:02:14,640 --> 00:02:16,400
I won’t let anyone take you away from me again.

14
00:02:16,400 --> 00:02:18,680
P’Sun has to be mine. Mine alone. I won’t let anyone...

15
00:02:19,040 --> 00:02:21,000
- Let go! Let go!
- Sun!

16
00:02:21,160 --> 00:02:23,120
I think you shouldn’t make this any bigger than it already is.

17
00:02:23,120 --> 00:02:24,720
Because if you hurt Fey,

18
00:02:24,720 --> 00:02:27,520
I won’t stop at just having you put on probation.

19
00:02:28,240 --> 00:02:30,760
So… who’s going to play the villain in this series?

20
00:02:30,760 --> 00:02:34,400
If she’s pairing up with Sun and Nop, she has to be a big name, right?

21
00:02:37,360 --> 00:02:39,440
Long time no see, Flint.

22
00:02:47,400 --> 00:02:49,400
How was the fitting today?

23
00:02:49,400 --> 00:02:51,400
This is just the fitting day,

24
00:02:51,640 --> 00:02:53,960
and the hashtag “SunNop”

25
00:02:53,960 --> 00:02:55,440
is already trending.

26
00:02:55,440 --> 00:02:58,480
I can’t imagine what it’ll be like when the series airs.

27
00:03:00,040 --> 00:03:01,480
The fitting went really well today, everyone.

28
00:03:01,480 --> 00:03:03,760
Since Sun and I are already close,

29
00:03:04,080 --> 00:03:06,360
so working together has been pretty easy for us.

30
00:03:06,680 --> 00:03:09,960
Close? How close exactly? Have you leveled up yet?

31
00:03:10,160 --> 00:03:11,120
I think…

32
00:03:11,440 --> 00:03:13,280
you should ask Sun

33
00:03:13,960 --> 00:03:15,960
when she’s going to let me level up.

34
00:03:18,960 --> 00:03:22,079
So, Sun? Nop has opened up this much.

35
00:03:22,400 --> 00:03:27,800
Or is the reason you haven’t opened your heart because you’re seeing someone?

36
00:03:28,280 --> 00:03:32,120
Uh… Sun doesn’t have anyone.

37
00:03:32,280 --> 00:03:34,280
Because if she did… I think…

38
00:03:34,280 --> 00:03:37,120
Our ship’s fans would be heartbroken, right?

39
00:03:38,040 --> 00:03:42,760
I heard about those dinner photos with Khun Rafah’s family.

40
00:03:43,040 --> 00:03:45,160
- So what’s the real story?
- Exactly, exactly!

41
00:03:45,880 --> 00:03:50,480
Believe it or not, Sun and I were just talking about how you’d definitely ask about this.

42
00:03:50,720 --> 00:03:52,000
Let me explain.

43
00:03:52,000 --> 00:03:56,040
Some of you may not know that Khun Paabfah is Sun’s close friend.

44
00:03:56,440 --> 00:03:58,880
Personally, I don’t see anything strange

45
00:03:58,880 --> 00:04:03,920
about Sun having dinner with Khun Rafah’s family as Paabfah’s close friend.

46
00:04:06,960 --> 00:04:09,760
Answered everything so thoroughly. Why not just do a solo interview instead?

47
00:04:11,960 --> 00:04:14,840
That day, Sun didn’t go as my sister’s close friend.

48
00:04:22,960 --> 00:04:24,960
She went as my girlfriend.

49
00:04:24,960 --> 00:04:26,320
What?!

50
00:04:36,240 --> 00:04:37,280
Congratulations.

51
00:04:57,640 --> 00:04:59,640
Long time no see, Flint.

52
00:05:05,560 --> 00:05:08,280
Nong Maya… don’t tell me...

53
00:05:13,920 --> 00:05:16,960
Yes. The villain everyone’s been speculating about…

54
00:05:20,160 --> 00:05:21,000
It’s me.

55
00:05:21,200 --> 00:05:22,800
Oh my…!

56
00:05:33,760 --> 00:05:35,760
I’m really sorry, Sun.

57
00:05:35,920 --> 00:05:39,480
I truly didn’t know that Maya was going to accept this role too.

58
00:05:39,800 --> 00:05:41,800
It’s not your fault, P’Mooham.

59
00:05:42,320 --> 00:05:45,600
Even if you had known, I would’ve still taken the role anyway.

60
00:05:46,040 --> 00:05:47,760
Please don’t blame yourself.

61
00:05:48,159 --> 00:05:49,920
But I still feel bad…

62
00:05:50,440 --> 00:05:52,040
Even though you say it’s fine,

63
00:05:52,320 --> 00:05:56,840
I know no one wants to work with their partner’s ex.

64
00:06:01,200 --> 00:06:02,600
Let’s go back to our room.

65
00:06:14,320 --> 00:06:16,680
Oh? You’re leaving already, P’Mooham?

66
00:06:19,240 --> 00:06:20,200
Yes…

67
00:06:20,400 --> 00:06:24,960
Maya, it’s been so long. You’re still as beautiful as ever.

68
00:06:25,240 --> 00:06:26,960
Not as beautiful as Sun, I’m sure.

69
00:06:26,960 --> 00:06:29,560
Come to think of it, you’ve really grown up.

70
00:06:30,080 --> 00:06:32,280
I never thought we’d get to work together one day.

71
00:06:33,000 --> 00:06:35,680
Please take good care of me.

72
00:06:35,960 --> 00:06:37,960
I should be the one saying that.

73
00:06:38,320 --> 00:06:42,720
If there’s anything you’d like to advise me on, P’Ya, I’d be more than happy to learn.

74
00:06:43,000 --> 00:06:46,520
Maya, the number one leading lady in the industry,

75
00:06:46,520 --> 00:06:48,840
probably doesn’t need to entrust herself to anyone.

76
00:06:50,120 --> 00:06:54,240
Actually, I’ve been wondering… why did you decide to take this role?

77
00:06:54,960 --> 00:06:59,560
Hmm… I accepted this role because the female lead

78
00:06:59,560 --> 00:07:01,880
is the angel of the entertainment industry.

79
00:07:02,160 --> 00:07:04,680
Anyone would want to work with her.

80
00:07:06,320 --> 00:07:08,000
Right, Flint?

81
00:07:10,960 --> 00:07:14,440
Uh… Maya, don’t you have another fitting session?

82
00:07:14,680 --> 00:07:19,200
Maybe we should head out so you don’t get home too late.

83
00:07:19,760 --> 00:07:22,480
Please take care of Sun and Khun Rafah.

84
00:07:23,360 --> 00:07:24,640
That’s already my responsibility.

85
00:07:26,080 --> 00:07:29,360
I’ll head back first, P’Ya. Goodbye.

86
00:07:50,760 --> 00:07:52,760
You’re still using the same number.

87
00:07:58,000 --> 00:08:01,280
Then… I’ll call you sometime, Flint.

88
00:08:18,600 --> 00:08:20,600
Thank you for driving me home.

89
00:08:25,040 --> 00:08:26,640
I told you to drop me at the house.

90
00:08:27,200 --> 00:08:28,000
So why...

91
00:08:34,159 --> 00:08:35,760
Where are you going?

92
00:08:37,919 --> 00:08:38,960
I’m hungry.

93
00:08:39,360 --> 00:08:40,200
But I’m not.

94
00:08:45,840 --> 00:08:46,560
Hey.

95
00:08:47,640 --> 00:08:48,440
Hey.

96
00:08:54,000 --> 00:08:55,360
Didn’t you say you were hungry?

97
00:08:56,480 --> 00:08:59,120
I only saw you order coffee. You didn’t eat anything.

98
00:09:00,000 --> 00:09:02,160
I never said I was hungry for food.

99
00:09:03,840 --> 00:09:06,800
If you were just going to order coffee, you could’ve gone through the drive-thru.

100
00:09:07,240 --> 00:09:08,480
You didn’t have to waste time coming with me.

101
00:09:09,160 --> 00:09:10,920
It’s not a waste of time.

102
00:09:11,360 --> 00:09:13,520
It’s Friday. The traffic’s insane.

103
00:09:14,640 --> 00:09:18,080
What about you? You haven’t eaten anything, have you? You’ll get a stomachache.

104
00:09:18,600 --> 00:09:20,920
You’re talking like you’re worried about me.

105
00:09:22,760 --> 00:09:23,400
I am.

106
00:09:27,320 --> 00:09:30,600
If you won’t take care of yourself, then I’ll worry about you instead.

107
00:09:48,800 --> 00:09:52,800
So… are you going to eat? If not, I’m calling for the check.

108
00:09:52,800 --> 00:09:56,280
Wait, are you embarrassed and pretending to be mad?

109
00:09:56,280 --> 00:09:58,160
Well… I saw you weren’t eating.

110
00:09:59,200 --> 00:10:00,680
I just didn’t want to waste the time.

111
00:10:02,320 --> 00:10:03,240
So? Are you eating or not?

112
00:10:08,360 --> 00:10:10,200
Long time no see, P’Peach.

113
00:10:11,040 --> 00:10:13,520
Cute? When did you get back to Thailand?

114
00:10:14,360 --> 00:10:20,680
Cute packed her bags and flew back the very morning
she woke up and didn’t find P’Peach lying next to her.

115
00:10:20,680 --> 00:10:22,840
Oh please, that’s an exaggeration, Love.

116
00:10:24,000 --> 00:10:27,320
Actually, Cute came to help oversee the work in Thailand for Khun Jeff.

117
00:10:28,120 --> 00:10:30,120
So I tagged along as company.

118
00:10:31,040 --> 00:10:32,280
Oh…

119
00:10:36,200 --> 00:10:39,920
Are we interrupting your dinner, P’Peach?

120
00:10:41,760 --> 00:10:43,160
I was just about to ask the same thing.

121
00:10:43,680 --> 00:10:45,840
If you’re going to stand here talking this long,

122
00:10:46,000 --> 00:10:47,640
why not join us at the table?

123
00:10:48,040 --> 00:10:48,920
Really?

124
00:10:56,360 --> 00:10:57,800
Just kidding.

125
00:10:58,560 --> 00:11:01,120
We won’t disturb you any further, P’Peach.

126
00:11:02,560 --> 00:11:04,000
It was nice seeing you.

127
00:11:08,680 --> 00:11:09,920
Khun Jeff…

128
00:11:10,320 --> 00:11:12,560
Is that the girl you’re shooting with tomorrow?

129
00:11:15,840 --> 00:11:18,160
See you tomorrow, P’Peach.

130
00:11:34,080 --> 00:11:36,080
Are you overthinking about Maya?

131
00:11:40,680 --> 00:11:43,360
Why would you think I am?

132
00:11:44,120 --> 00:11:46,120
Because if I were you…

133
00:11:47,280 --> 00:11:50,280
I wouldn’t feel very good hearing her say things like that.

134
00:11:51,440 --> 00:11:55,160
I’m asking because I’m worried about you.

135
00:12:09,200 --> 00:12:10,960
Thank you for worrying about me.

136
00:12:13,120 --> 00:12:16,080
But… you and Maya used to date.

137
00:12:16,880 --> 00:12:20,880
It wouldn’t be strange if she called you, right?

138
00:12:23,320 --> 00:12:24,840
You should answer her call.

139
00:12:36,360 --> 00:12:38,680
I’ll only answer if you’re here with me.

140
00:12:46,960 --> 00:12:48,640
Go ahead. You can say whatever you want.

141
00:12:49,200 --> 00:12:51,200
I thought you weren’t going to pick up my call.

142
00:12:51,600 --> 00:12:54,400
Why are you being so distant with your ex, Flint?

143
00:12:55,200 --> 00:12:57,960
Or is it because… now that you have a new girlfriend,

144
00:12:58,320 --> 00:13:01,240
you can’t talk to someone familiar like me anymore?

145
00:13:07,680 --> 00:13:10,600
You’re awfully quiet… Are you together right now?

146
00:13:11,440 --> 00:13:14,560
Sorry for interrupting your private time, Sun.

147
00:13:15,600 --> 00:13:16,840
You’re not interrupting.

148
00:13:18,320 --> 00:13:19,840
Please, go ahead.

149
00:13:25,560 --> 00:13:26,720
Flint.

150
00:13:32,480 --> 00:13:34,000
What do you want, Maya?

151
00:13:34,080 --> 00:13:36,080
Don’t use that harsh tone with me.

152
00:13:36,080 --> 00:13:38,400
I just got back to Thailand,

153
00:13:38,720 --> 00:13:40,400
and I don’t have a car yet.

154
00:13:40,720 --> 00:13:42,720
I’m thinking of buying one.

155
00:13:43,040 --> 00:13:45,400
So tomorrow, I’d like you to help me pick one out.

156
00:13:46,080 --> 00:13:49,720
I hope… you won’t refuse this customer.

157
00:13:49,720 --> 00:13:51,640
You can think of it as helping your ex.

158
00:13:51,640 --> 00:13:54,960
You probably know best which car suits me.

159
00:14:02,480 --> 00:14:06,400
Hey. Can you stop looking at your phone and drive me home, please?

160
00:14:07,680 --> 00:14:11,080
Or if you’re not convenient because you’d rather go to dinner with your ex,

161
00:14:11,720 --> 00:14:13,720
I can call someone else to pick me up.

162
00:14:17,960 --> 00:14:19,000
Ex?

163
00:14:20,280 --> 00:14:22,120
If you mean Cute,

164
00:14:22,120 --> 00:14:25,440
she’s not my ex.

165
00:14:28,920 --> 00:14:30,400
Well, I didn’t know.

166
00:14:30,400 --> 00:14:34,160
Her friend said she woke up and didn’t find you in bed,

167
00:14:34,480 --> 00:14:36,480
so she rushed back to Thailand to follow you.

168
00:14:36,920 --> 00:14:40,080
I was afraid that if she really were your ex,

169
00:14:40,920 --> 00:14:42,920
she might misunderstand me.

170
00:14:44,000 --> 00:14:47,000
Sharing a bed doesn’t automatically mean we’re dating.

171
00:15:00,840 --> 00:15:02,840
Even if Sun says it’s fine,

172
00:15:02,840 --> 00:15:07,000
I know no one wants to work with their partner’s ex.

173
00:15:27,920 --> 00:15:29,920
I am about to finish.

174
00:15:31,480 --> 00:15:33,040
Can you stay with me for a while?

175
00:15:39,360 --> 00:15:43,600
Tomorrow… can I go to work with you?

176
00:15:45,080 --> 00:15:47,440
Isn’t P'Maya coming to see you tomorrow?

177
00:15:53,040 --> 00:15:57,520
Do you realize you’re acting like someone who feels guilty?

178
00:15:59,240 --> 00:16:02,840
I’m not doing this because I’m guilty.

179
00:16:04,160 --> 00:16:05,840
I’m doing this

180
00:16:06,800 --> 00:16:08,800
because I know you’re uncomfortable.

181
00:16:20,560 --> 00:16:22,920
You’re arguing with me in your head right now, aren’t you?

182
00:16:33,320 --> 00:16:37,040
What Maya and I had ended a long time ago.

183
00:16:38,560 --> 00:16:40,920
Even if you say it’s okay,

184
00:16:43,800 --> 00:16:45,160
I know

185
00:16:46,040 --> 00:16:48,040
what she did today

186
00:16:49,520 --> 00:16:51,000
will make you overthink.

187
00:16:53,240 --> 00:16:55,520
But I want you to know something.

188
00:16:56,760 --> 00:16:58,760
I will never...

189
00:17:00,800 --> 00:17:02,640
ever make you sad

190
00:17:05,079 --> 00:17:07,079
or disappoint you again.

191
00:17:20,160 --> 00:17:22,160
I’m sorry

192
00:17:25,359 --> 00:17:27,359
for making you feel uneasy.

193
00:17:41,880 --> 00:17:43,880
Can you trust me?

194
00:17:52,560 --> 00:17:54,560
I’m sorry…

195
00:17:56,840 --> 00:18:00,080
if I acted childish toward you.

196
00:18:03,600 --> 00:18:05,280
It’s just that…

197
00:18:06,000 --> 00:18:09,240
I went through a lot today.

198
00:18:14,200 --> 00:18:16,200
You’re not mad at me, right?

199
00:18:19,800 --> 00:18:22,160
How could I be mad at someone I love?

200
00:18:25,400 --> 00:18:27,400
Good girl

201
00:20:13,440 --> 00:20:15,120
I’ll pick you up at ten tomorrow.

202
00:20:17,440 --> 00:20:19,240
As for me checking my phone…

203
00:20:19,240 --> 00:20:23,080
I was counting how many rules I’ve already broken.

204
00:20:25,360 --> 00:20:26,200
What rules?

205
00:20:26,480 --> 00:20:31,240
Normally, I don’t have dinner with someone
or drive them home more than once if I’m not interested.

206
00:20:31,680 --> 00:20:34,000
But you’ve already exceeded my quota.

207
00:20:35,160 --> 00:20:35,840
But…

208
00:20:36,400 --> 00:20:38,200
I never asked you to do any of that.

209
00:20:38,560 --> 00:20:39,440
Exactly.

210
00:20:40,000 --> 00:20:42,280
So that means… I’m interested in you.

211
00:20:54,800 --> 00:20:57,800
You don’t have to pick me up. I can go by myself.

212
00:20:59,960 --> 00:21:01,400
Good night.

213
00:21:13,880 --> 00:21:16,880
- Yesterday, right in the middle of the press interview!
- What happened, P’Oui?

214
00:21:16,880 --> 00:21:18,880
- Khun Rafah Supawaret.
- Yes.

215
00:21:18,880 --> 00:21:23,000
- The famous luxury car importer made it official!
- Wow!

216
00:21:23,000 --> 00:21:25,520
She announced that she’s dating a leading actress.

217
00:21:25,520 --> 00:21:27,800
- Who is it, P’Oui?
- It’s Sun Atita!

218
00:21:27,800 --> 00:21:29,400
And at that exact moment, viewers

219
00:21:29,400 --> 00:21:33,720
because as soon as Khun Rafah made the announcement,

220
00:21:33,720 --> 00:21:37,160
Maya appeared. She’s the number one leading lady,

221
00:21:37,160 --> 00:21:42,320
and also Khun Rafah’s ex. She disappeared from the industry for almost two years.

222
00:21:43,040 --> 00:21:48,960
Now she’s back as an actress on the same channel as Sun Atita.

223
00:21:54,760 --> 00:21:57,160
You’re calling about the news, right?

224
00:21:57,600 --> 00:22:00,640
I just found out Khun Maya is acting in this series too.

225
00:22:01,560 --> 00:22:02,760
Are you okay, Sun?

226
00:22:03,480 --> 00:22:04,480
Of course I am.

227
00:22:05,160 --> 00:22:07,120
I already talked to Flint.

228
00:22:07,600 --> 00:22:10,600
And… I’ve decided

229
00:22:11,040 --> 00:22:13,080
that I’m going to trust her.

230
00:22:13,880 --> 00:22:15,120
Don’t worry about me.

231
00:22:16,000 --> 00:22:19,280
If you feel uncomfortable about anything, call me anytime, okay?

232
00:22:19,960 --> 00:22:21,480
Uh, Fey…

233
00:22:22,200 --> 00:22:23,760
Are you going into the company today?

234
00:22:23,760 --> 00:22:25,760
I have a shoot with Peach today.

235
00:22:26,680 --> 00:22:28,120
Are you coming to see me at the office?

236
00:22:28,600 --> 00:22:30,120
Just asking.

237
00:22:31,000 --> 00:22:33,160
We’ll talk later. Bye.

238
00:22:43,160 --> 00:22:47,400
So today… do you let me go to work with you?

239
00:22:55,760 --> 00:22:59,880
I have a workshop at the station today. You should go to the office, P’Flint.

240
00:23:00,600 --> 00:23:02,240
I can go with P’Mooham.

241
00:23:09,560 --> 00:23:12,680
Thank you… for trusting me.

242
00:23:24,800 --> 00:23:26,800
Is Fey awake yet?

243
00:24:01,720 --> 00:24:05,320
Have someone prepare the car for me. I don’t really feel like driving today.

244
00:24:05,320 --> 00:24:07,560
Um… Khun Fey?

245
00:24:07,560 --> 00:24:08,360
Yes?

246
00:24:08,360 --> 00:24:10,360
Oh, perfect timing.

247
00:24:10,360 --> 00:24:12,680
P’Peach has been waiting outside for quite a while.

248
00:24:13,240 --> 00:24:16,280
So I invited her in for coffee.

249
00:24:24,240 --> 00:24:27,400
Shall we go, Nong Fey?

250
00:24:44,840 --> 00:24:46,880
- Please take her to get dressed.
- Sure thing.

251
00:24:46,880 --> 00:24:48,080
I’ll wait at the set.

252
00:24:48,440 --> 00:24:49,920
Uh… okay.

253
00:24:51,960 --> 00:24:55,440
Hey. When are you going to stop calling me “Nong”?

254
00:24:55,720 --> 00:24:59,120
Your mom told me to call you Nong Fey.

255
00:24:59,760 --> 00:25:02,000
If I call you “Khun,” it feels distant.

256
00:25:02,920 --> 00:25:04,280
Then this time…

257
00:25:04,920 --> 00:25:07,040
why don’t you try calling me P’Peach?

258
00:25:07,760 --> 00:25:08,880
No.

259
00:25:11,160 --> 00:25:14,440
You two look pretty close like a photographer and his model who are very comfortable with each other.

260
00:25:15,840 --> 00:25:19,680
Or… are you close in the same way you’re close with her, Cute?

261
00:25:20,760 --> 00:25:22,560
You should be careful with P’Peach.

262
00:25:22,560 --> 00:25:24,920
She likes breaking girls’ hearts for fun.

263
00:25:26,240 --> 00:25:28,240
Don’t blame her like that.

264
00:25:28,680 --> 00:25:33,320
Maybe some girls are willing. Like me.

265
00:25:36,600 --> 00:25:39,840
Sorry I didn’t greet you properly yesterday.

266
00:25:40,360 --> 00:25:41,480
It’s fine.

267
00:25:43,880 --> 00:25:45,480
I’ll go get my makeup done first so we can finish shooting quickly.

268
00:25:45,680 --> 00:25:47,120
I’ll come help

269
00:25:47,840 --> 00:25:51,880
in case there’s any problem I can fix.

270
00:25:55,000 --> 00:25:57,000
Maybe you should fix your own problem first.

271
00:25:57,800 --> 00:25:59,120
Like how you're gonna fix it.

272
00:26:00,800 --> 00:26:01,760
Excuse me.

273
00:26:18,560 --> 00:26:19,960
Hello, Khun Rafah.

274
00:26:22,080 --> 00:26:23,640
I’ve arrived.

275
00:26:23,960 --> 00:26:25,680
Once you finish work, I’ll go pick you up.

276
00:26:29,400 --> 00:26:30,640
How is everything?

277
00:26:31,040 --> 00:26:33,400
Um… Khun Maya has been waiting to see you since this morning.

278
00:26:33,520 --> 00:26:36,000
Right now, I’ve asked her to wait in the lounge.

279
00:26:36,000 --> 00:26:37,680
Just as you instructed, Khun Rafah.

280
00:26:40,400 --> 00:26:42,040
Have someone from Sales meet me in my office.

281
00:26:42,640 --> 00:26:43,520
Yes, ma’am.

282
00:26:55,240 --> 00:26:58,040
How did you know I was here?

283
00:26:59,200 --> 00:27:01,160
It wasn’t that hard to figure out.

284
00:27:07,720 --> 00:27:12,120
So that means… you still understand me like you used to?

285
00:27:18,400 --> 00:27:20,400
I’d say I understand your habits more than anything.

286
00:27:28,960 --> 00:27:31,480
Excuse me, the documents are ready.

287
00:27:32,240 --> 00:27:34,240
Are you afraid of being alone with me,

288
00:27:34,760 --> 00:27:36,960
that you had to bring an employee in as backup?

289
00:27:37,640 --> 00:27:40,000
You said you came to look at cars, didn’t you?

290
00:27:40,600 --> 00:27:42,360
So I had my staff assist you.

291
00:27:44,240 --> 00:27:48,240
Don’t tell me you really don’t know why I’m here.

292
00:27:50,640 --> 00:27:54,360
A top-tier businesswoman with a doctorate like you

293
00:27:54,840 --> 00:27:57,760
should easily understand what I want, shouldn’t you?

294
00:28:07,720 --> 00:28:09,440
What do you want, Maya?

295
00:28:15,320 --> 00:28:16,920
If I tell you…

296
00:28:19,480 --> 00:28:21,360
will you give me what I want?

297
00:28:23,680 --> 00:28:27,040
What’s wrong? Are you worried about your new girlfriend?

298
00:28:29,040 --> 00:28:30,640
To be honest,

299
00:28:31,360 --> 00:28:34,840
I never thought you’d take your sister’s best friend

300
00:28:35,480 --> 00:28:37,480
- and turn her into your
-Stop right there, Maya.

301
00:28:37,880 --> 00:28:39,120
Why?

302
00:28:39,120 --> 00:28:40,640
Is she untouchable now?

303
00:28:41,600 --> 00:28:43,680
Do you love your new girlfriend that much?

304
00:28:44,160 --> 00:28:45,360
Yes.

305
00:28:46,320 --> 00:28:47,840
And what you shouldn’t forget

306
00:28:49,080 --> 00:28:51,080
is that what we had is over.

307
00:28:53,280 --> 00:28:55,280
The only reason I agreed to meet you today

308
00:28:56,360 --> 00:29:01,360
was to apologize for dragging you into that relationship in the first place.

309
00:29:02,000 --> 00:29:06,120
You’re talking as if you’re admitting that all this time, you were
just using me as Sun’s substitute.

310
00:29:06,720 --> 00:29:07,800
Is that it, Flint?

311
00:29:11,080 --> 00:29:12,520
How clear.

312
00:29:14,040 --> 00:29:17,600
Well then… I hope you’re happy with this new love of yours, Flint.

313
00:29:24,520 --> 00:29:26,520
You haven’t forgotten, have you,

314
00:29:27,360 --> 00:29:29,360
why we broke up?

315
00:29:32,080 --> 00:29:34,480
Be careful… or history might repeat itself.

316
00:29:49,680 --> 00:29:53,000
Does Khun Rafah know that you were summoned by the executives?

317
00:29:53,960 --> 00:29:56,720
I only told P’Flint I had a workshop.

318
00:29:59,200 --> 00:30:02,400
At the very least, she should be aware

319
00:30:02,720 --> 00:30:06,120
that what she’s doing might put Sun in a difficult position.

320
00:30:06,480 --> 00:30:08,680
I’ve worked here for years

321
00:30:08,680 --> 00:30:11,960
and I’ve never been called in by management this often.

322
00:30:12,480 --> 00:30:14,840
I’m sorry, P’Mooham.

323
00:30:19,400 --> 00:30:20,920
Hello.

324
00:30:31,360 --> 00:30:33,360
We’ve been seeing each other quite often lately.

325
00:30:33,960 --> 00:30:35,080
Do you know why?

326
00:30:37,600 --> 00:30:40,920
I’m sorry for letting this happen.

327
00:30:41,880 --> 00:30:43,360
The leaked photos

328
00:30:43,880 --> 00:30:48,360
I understand they can’t be one hundred percent confirmed to be Sun.

329
00:30:48,840 --> 00:30:50,840
But this time, it’s not like before.

330
00:30:51,640 --> 00:30:53,120
I understand.

331
00:30:53,560 --> 00:30:57,760
If you knew, why didn’t you inform the channel before acting?

332
00:30:58,400 --> 00:30:59,560
I’m sorry.

333
00:31:00,080 --> 00:31:03,760
And if what happened causes damage to the channel,

334
00:31:04,080 --> 00:31:06,440
I’m willing to pay compensation according to my contract.

335
00:31:23,840 --> 00:31:25,840
It seems both you and Khun Rafah

336
00:31:27,080 --> 00:31:30,240
are quite willing to pay the penalty.

337
00:31:33,240 --> 00:31:35,520
But this time, I’ll consider you lucky

338
00:31:36,920 --> 00:31:39,560
the public reaction hasn’t been negative.

339
00:31:42,720 --> 00:31:46,680
And I hope this will be the last time

340
00:31:46,920 --> 00:31:49,880
you do something without informing the channel.

341
00:31:50,920 --> 00:31:52,760
You understand what I’m saying, right?

342
00:32:27,000 --> 00:32:29,760
I remember that you doesn’t eat breakfast either,

343
00:32:30,080 --> 00:32:31,600
so I ordered coffee for you.

344
00:32:32,480 --> 00:32:33,960
Thank you.

345
00:32:33,960 --> 00:32:36,880
But lately I’ve been going to the gym,

346
00:32:38,000 --> 00:32:39,360
so I’m only drinking milk.

347
00:32:42,960 --> 00:32:47,400
Oh, and the references I sent, are you okay with them?

348
00:32:47,400 --> 00:32:51,960
I think your work already meets high standards.

349
00:32:52,320 --> 00:32:55,600
The gallery probably won’t need many adjustments.

350
00:32:55,880 --> 00:32:57,200
Right, Cute?

351
00:32:58,440 --> 00:33:00,800
The gallery may not need anything.

352
00:33:01,000 --> 00:33:02,360
But I do.

353
00:33:19,680 --> 00:33:22,560
If what you need… is me

354
00:33:22,960 --> 00:33:24,840
I guess I should tell you…

355
00:33:24,840 --> 00:33:26,600
I already have a date.

356
00:33:39,200 --> 00:33:41,200
I’ve solved the problem for you.

357
00:34:02,320 --> 00:34:03,880
What are you doing!?

358
00:34:05,160 --> 00:34:07,160
Just giving you some encouragement before work.

359
00:34:08,679 --> 00:34:10,679
- Hey, you
- Want more encouragement?

360
00:34:20,440 --> 00:34:21,560
Thanks.

361
00:34:26,280 --> 00:34:31,480
You and Khun Paabfah don’t really look like people who are dating, do they?

362
00:34:32,000 --> 00:34:34,760
Honestly… you should already know

363
00:34:35,120 --> 00:34:38,040
that P'Peach has never seriously dated anyone.

364
00:34:38,560 --> 00:34:41,320
But whether you're dating or not…

365
00:34:41,960 --> 00:34:43,040
I don't mind.

366
00:34:43,880 --> 00:34:46,639
I can accept all of P’Peach’s conditions.

367
00:34:48,080 --> 00:34:49,080
But I do.

368
00:34:49,480 --> 00:34:52,159
I’m not comfortable dating multiple people at the same time.

369
00:34:52,800 --> 00:34:56,679
Love, you already know I’ve never seriously dated anyone.

370
00:34:57,360 --> 00:35:01,320
After all… you came to see me right after the night Cute stayed over, didn’t you?

371
00:35:14,000 --> 00:35:17,160
Mooham, go inform PR

372
00:35:17,160 --> 00:35:21,600
to prepare a workshop feature on Sun and Nop.

373
00:35:21,920 --> 00:35:24,480
Okay, I’ll excuse myself.

374
00:35:31,720 --> 00:35:33,720
I understand

375
00:35:34,480 --> 00:35:38,480
that between Sun and Khun Rafah pairing is getting great feedback.

376
00:35:39,080 --> 00:35:40,560
But this series

377
00:35:40,960 --> 00:35:43,520
is co-produced with Korea.

378
00:35:43,800 --> 00:35:45,320
And they agreed

379
00:35:45,840 --> 00:35:50,560
because they wanted a rising on-screen couple like Sun and Nop.

380
00:35:55,400 --> 00:35:58,560
If any more problems arise from now on,

381
00:35:59,000 --> 00:36:02,800
I’ll have no choice but to assign someone else to manage Sun.

382
00:36:03,320 --> 00:36:04,560
Please understand.

383
00:36:28,920 --> 00:36:30,280
Sun,

384
00:36:31,240 --> 00:36:34,200
why did you come out without waiting for me?

385
00:36:34,520 --> 00:36:39,680
Did anything happen while I wasn’t there?

386
00:36:39,880 --> 00:36:41,120
No.

387
00:36:41,480 --> 00:36:43,840
Shall we head into the workshop room?

388
00:36:44,200 --> 00:36:45,160
Let’s go.

389
00:36:50,800 --> 00:36:52,440
Hello.

390
00:36:52,880 --> 00:36:56,400
Yes, Sun has a workshop with Nop at the station today.

391
00:36:58,200 --> 00:37:02,240
Maya isn’t at the station today.

392
00:37:02,960 --> 00:37:04,280
What?

393
00:37:04,280 --> 00:37:05,400
What post?

394
00:37:09,960 --> 00:37:13,600
“Thank you for always taking care of me. You haven’t changed at all.”

395
00:37:16,760 --> 00:37:18,760
What are you looking at?

396
00:37:20,200 --> 00:37:22,200
Is that Maya’s latest post?

397
00:37:22,600 --> 00:37:27,320
At first, I thought she skipped the workshop because she had something important.

398
00:37:27,680 --> 00:37:29,680
Turns out she’s with Khun Rafah.

399
00:37:30,240 --> 00:37:31,760
Sun, you’re so generous.

400
00:37:31,760 --> 00:37:33,960
Letting your girlfriend go back to see her ex like that.

401
00:37:38,120 --> 00:37:41,000
Maybe we should hurry into the workshop.

402
00:37:41,240 --> 00:37:44,360
The PR team will be here soon to film a feature.

403
00:37:46,440 --> 00:37:47,600
Let’s go, Sun.

404
00:38:21,400 --> 00:38:23,040
Why are you up so early, Flint?

405
00:38:38,000 --> 00:38:40,000
Were you secretly checking my phone?

406
00:38:40,520 --> 00:38:42,520
I’m sorry for being rude.

407
00:38:48,720 --> 00:38:52,640
But if I have to choose between being rude and being a fool,

408
00:38:53,880 --> 00:38:56,520
I’d rather be rude.

409
00:38:58,680 --> 00:39:00,200
Why, Flint?

410
00:39:01,200 --> 00:39:03,800
You’ve never been jealous of me before.

411
00:39:04,200 --> 00:39:06,040
No matter how good I was to you,

412
00:39:07,080 --> 00:39:09,840
it was never enough to make you come back to me.

413
00:39:10,680 --> 00:39:14,760
You made me feel like you were never serious about me.

414
00:39:15,840 --> 00:39:17,240
And the reason you’re acting like this now

415
00:39:18,200 --> 00:39:21,880
is because you’re angry you were cheated on… isn’t it?

416
00:39:23,160 --> 00:39:25,760
I’m sorry for everything that happened, Maya.

417
00:39:27,360 --> 00:39:28,800
But let’s end this here.

418
00:39:29,520 --> 00:39:31,160
Remember this,

419
00:39:32,080 --> 00:39:34,360
someone who doesn’t understand love like you

420
00:39:35,200 --> 00:39:37,520
won’t find anyone who can endure you the way I did.

421
00:40:22,560 --> 00:40:26,400
Thank you… for letting me know what it feels like to be deceived.

422
00:40:27,480 --> 00:40:29,480
It’s done, P’Peach.

423
00:40:42,880 --> 00:40:45,160
I think you look better without the glasses.

424
00:40:48,920 --> 00:40:50,880
Can you please stop doing this?

425
00:40:51,840 --> 00:40:52,480
Doing what?

426
00:40:53,120 --> 00:40:56,800
Acting like nothing happened... when you just...

427
00:40:56,800 --> 00:40:57,840
Kissed?

428
00:40:59,480 --> 00:41:03,120
Go on, Nong Fey. Say it. Say that I just kissed you.

429
00:41:06,920 --> 00:41:08,120
Will you stop joking?

430
00:41:08,360 --> 00:41:11,920
I’m not someone who just… kisses anyone like you do.

431
00:41:13,920 --> 00:41:17,440
Last time, you kissed me first. I didn’t complain.

432
00:41:18,760 --> 00:41:20,280
I did not kiss you.

433
00:41:21,160 --> 00:41:23,600
And I only kiss the person I’m dating.

434
00:41:23,800 --> 00:41:26,560
Why don’t you fix your own problem by yourself?

435
00:41:26,880 --> 00:41:28,000
What problem?

436
00:41:28,720 --> 00:41:30,920
I don’t see any problem at all.

437
00:41:31,120 --> 00:41:32,120
It’s you…

438
00:41:36,000 --> 00:41:36,920
Who are you looking for?

439
00:41:39,160 --> 00:41:41,040
Just now, Nong Fey said

440
00:41:41,440 --> 00:41:43,640
You only kisses the person you’re dating.

441
00:41:44,840 --> 00:41:45,880
In that case…

442
00:41:47,560 --> 00:41:49,400
would you date me?

443
00:42:19,840 --> 00:42:20,880
Hello?

444
00:42:21,680 --> 00:42:24,480
Are you done with work, Sun? I’ll head out to pick you up.

445
00:42:25,400 --> 00:42:26,640
I’m done.

446
00:42:29,320 --> 00:42:30,040
Khun Jan…

447
00:42:32,880 --> 00:42:36,360
You’re good. You can even recognize voices.

448
00:42:39,080 --> 00:42:40,800
May I speak to Sun?

449
00:42:41,520 --> 00:42:43,240
Who is it, P’Jan?

450
00:42:46,800 --> 00:42:48,160
Your good girl’s calling.

451
00:43:01,360 --> 00:43:02,560
Yes, P’Flint.

452
00:43:03,800 --> 00:43:05,840
Why didn’t you tell me you were done?

453
00:43:06,400 --> 00:43:07,600
I could’ve gone to pick you up.

454
00:43:08,880 --> 00:43:09,960
It’s okay…

455
00:43:10,640 --> 00:43:16,360
I was worried you might be busy, so P’Jan and P’Win came instead.

456
00:43:19,280 --> 00:43:22,240
Then I’ll pick you up at Khun Jan’s condo.

457
00:43:23,680 --> 00:43:25,640
You don’t have to.

458
00:43:26,200 --> 00:43:29,520
P’Jan asked me to stay over tonight.

459
00:43:30,880 --> 00:43:32,880
We’ll see each other tomorrow.

460
00:43:34,280 --> 00:43:36,240
I hope you don’t have a problem with that.

461
00:43:37,560 --> 00:43:42,240
Even my sister doesn’t have a problem with what you’re doing.

462
00:43:43,040 --> 00:43:43,880
P’Jan…

463
00:43:48,720 --> 00:43:52,520
That’s fine. I’ll see you tomorrow then.

464
00:44:11,360 --> 00:44:12,760
Did you see it?

465
00:44:16,080 --> 00:44:17,800
Yes, I saw it.

466
00:44:19,520 --> 00:44:24,280
Don’t let trust turn around and hurt you, Sun.

467
00:44:26,160 --> 00:44:28,320
I may have just returned to Thailand,

468
00:44:28,960 --> 00:44:33,400
but digging into Khun Rafah and her ex isn’t difficult.

469
00:44:46,320 --> 00:44:48,880
You didn’t have to walk me all the way in.

470
00:44:49,160 --> 00:44:51,920
This is my house. I can walk by myself.

471
00:44:52,600 --> 00:44:56,240
I promised your mother I’d take good care of you.

472
00:44:56,720 --> 00:44:58,720
So I walked you in.

473
00:45:00,280 --> 00:45:03,280
Then… aren’t you going to walk me to my room too?

474
00:45:03,280 --> 00:45:04,040
May I?

475
00:45:06,080 --> 00:45:07,920
These days you even walk each other into the house?

476
00:45:11,440 --> 00:45:15,480
Or… are Fey and Khun Peach really dating?

477
00:45:18,800 --> 00:45:20,160
Oh my...! P’Flint.

478
00:45:20,160 --> 00:45:24,200
You know you and P’Peach have the same type.

479
00:45:24,880 --> 00:45:27,040
How could she possibly like me?

480
00:45:28,600 --> 00:45:29,800
I do.

481
00:45:32,520 --> 00:45:36,360
If you don’t mind, Khun Flint, may I court your sister?

482
00:45:39,600 --> 00:45:43,760
That’s something you should ask my sister.

483
00:45:45,880 --> 00:45:50,720
But judging from the fact that she kissed you and lets you pick her up and drop her off…

484
00:45:51,760 --> 00:45:53,760
I think she likes you too.

485
00:45:55,400 --> 00:45:56,520
Try harder.

486
00:45:56,920 --> 00:46:00,640
Being stubborn runs in our family.

487
00:46:05,240 --> 00:46:05,960
P’Flint!!!

488
00:46:07,840 --> 00:46:10,160
Consider that I've passed the first round.

489
00:46:10,720 --> 00:46:11,960
See you tomorrow.

490
00:46:16,640 --> 00:46:18,240
Oh, I almost forgot.

491
00:46:18,680 --> 00:46:19,960
Good night.

492
00:46:49,760 --> 00:46:54,040
Don’t let trust turn around and hurt you, Sun.

493
00:46:58,120 --> 00:46:59,960
She disappeared for two years

494
00:46:59,960 --> 00:47:01,440
and suddenly came back now.

495
00:47:01,440 --> 00:47:03,440
Do you really not know what she wants?

496
00:47:04,240 --> 00:47:06,880
Do you really think you can trust your person completely?

497
00:47:58,720 --> 00:48:00,720
(Sweet dreams.)

498
00:50:15,240 --> 00:50:17,240
Dear Diary,

499
00:50:17,240 --> 00:50:19,520
My life has been so chaotic lately.

500
00:50:19,880 --> 00:50:22,320
It started as just “giving it a try,”

501
00:50:22,480 --> 00:50:25,000
but now I have so much work.

502
00:50:25,360 --> 00:50:30,120
Some days I’m so busy I barely even have time to eat.

503
00:50:30,120 --> 00:50:33,520
You must be lonely, wondering what I’ve been up to.

504
00:50:33,520 --> 00:50:35,520
The truth is…

505
00:50:35,720 --> 00:50:38,040
I’ve become someone’s dream.

506
00:50:38,360 --> 00:50:40,360
But maybe not for P’Flint.

507
00:50:40,760 --> 00:50:44,440
I worked so hard to get here.

508
00:50:44,920 --> 00:50:48,840
Yet somehow, it makes me feel further and further away from her…

509
00:50:49,440 --> 00:50:51,120
Sun, what’s going on with that clip?

510
00:50:51,120 --> 00:50:52,920
The girl in the video looks a lot like you.

511
00:50:52,920 --> 00:50:54,720
And who’s the man in the clip?

512
00:50:54,720 --> 00:50:57,720
I told you before, didn’t I? Don’t let any more problems happen.

513
00:50:57,720 --> 00:50:59,320
Why didn’t you listen?

514
00:50:59,320 --> 00:51:03,600
If we’re going to punish someone, shouldn’t there be a clear investigation first?

515
00:51:03,600 --> 00:51:06,040
How strange… running into you here, Flint.

516
00:51:06,480 --> 00:51:07,400
Stop pretending.

517
00:51:09,400 --> 00:51:10,760
- Sun
- I’m sorry.

518
00:51:11,600 --> 00:51:15,720
That day, I wasn’t brave enough to tell you how I truly felt.

519
00:51:17,480 --> 00:51:21,440
I believe Khun Rafah is probably trying to find a solution too.

520
00:51:22,440 --> 00:51:23,360
Oh, Sun.

521
00:51:24,000 --> 00:51:25,440
You came without telling me.

522
00:51:26,680 --> 00:51:29,040
I don’t know what I’m supposed to do anymore, Fey.

523
00:51:29,480 --> 00:51:33,640
What I’m most afraid of… is being diminished by the person I love the most.

524
00:51:34,200 --> 00:51:35,680
Why hasn’t P’Flint gone to see Sun?

525
00:51:36,480 --> 00:51:39,440
Everything I did, I did it for you.

526
00:51:40,240 --> 00:51:41,880
After just publicly announcing your relationship,

527
00:51:41,880 --> 00:51:45,040
and then this clip comes out. Has it shaken your relationship?
